The paper discusses multi-head finite automata, which are a topic in formal language theory and automata theory. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses computational and descriptional complexity issues, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions undecidable and non-semi-decidable problems, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper discusses alternative characterizations of multi-head finite automata, which could also place it in cs.IT (Information Theory).
